    <summary>Windows-native screen / application / region recorder with an NVIDIA NVENC pipeline, multi-track audio, and diagnostics.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/Exoridus/exosnap/releases/tag/v0.4.0</releaseNotes>
    <description><![CDATA[
ExoSnap is a Windows-native screen / application / region recorder built around a
high-performance NVIDIA NVENC pipeline, flexible container/codec profiles,
multi-track audio routing, a webcam overlay, and built-in diagnostics.

This package downloads and installs the official ExoSnap 0.4.0 MSI from the
project's GitHub Release.

## Highlights

* Capture an application window, a monitor, or a screen region at CFR 60 fps.
* NVIDIA NVENC hardware encoding: H.264 and AV1.
* Multi-track audio (`APP`, `SYS`, `MIC`) with reorderable / mergeable layout.
* Containers: MKV (default), WebM, MP4. Audio: AAC-LC, Opus.
* Webcam picture-in-picture overlay, recording presets, rebindable global hotkeys.
* Diagnostics-first: invalid recordings are blocked before start.
* **0.4.0 new:** local-first crash capture (out-of-process Crashpad) with a
  privacy-scrubbed, consent-gated next-launch crash report (assisted GitHub issue or
  opt-in Sentry upload with EU data residency); update checking with Stable / Preview
  channels (signed manifest: ed25519 + SHA-256; notify + open releases page, no silent
  restart).

## Requirements

* Windows 10/11 x64.
* An NVIDIA GPU with supported NVENC (AMD/Intel/software encoding are not supported in 0.4.0).
* Microsoft Visual C++ 2022 x64 runtime.

## Pre-v1 notice

ExoSnap 0.4.0 is a pre-v1 preview. Settings, preset, and recording-history file
formats are not frozen and may change incompatibly before 1.0.0.
]]></description>
    <!-- exosnap.exe and the shipped Qt6 DLLs link the dynamic MSVC runtime (/MD);
         the MSI does not bundle vcruntime140/msvcp140. Without this dependency a
         clean machine fails to launch with STATUS_DLL_NOT_FOUND (0xC0000135). -->
    <dependencies>
      <!-- Minimum 14.30 (VS 2022 baseline): ExoSnap statically imports
           msvcp140_atomic_wait.dll (added in 14.28) and the other VC++
           2015-2022 runtime DLLs, so an older redistributable is insufficient. -->
      <dependency id="vcredist140" version="14.30.30704" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
